==\nThe countries and [[international organization]]s that have sent aid and funds to [[Government of Serbia]], to help fight the pandemic:\n\n* {{Flag|People's Republic of China}} have first donated [[Serbia]] [[COVID-19 testing|COVID-19 tests]] and sent [[National Health Commission|medical staff]], who have experience with combating the disease in [[Guangdong]] province.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.blic.rs/vesti/drustvo/ambasadorka-cen-bo-prijatelji-stigla-vam-je-pomoc-iz-prvih-redova-borbe-vucic-srbija/623sc7s|title=Ambasadorka \u010cen Bo: Prijatelji, stigla vam je pomo\u0107 iz PRVIH REDOVA BORBE Vu\u010di\u0107: Srbija ovo NE SME DA ZABORAVI|last=I.M.J|first=M. V. J. , Marko Mijailovi\u0107|website=Blic.rs|language=sr|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nedeljnik.rs/pomoc-iz-kine-u-srbiju-stigli-testovi-za-koronavirus/|title=Pomo\u0107 iz Kine: U Srbiju stigli testovi za koronavirus|last=Nedeljnik.rs|date=2020-03-16|website=Nedeljnik|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|Norway}} On 20 March, the Norwegian ambassador to Serbia Jern Eugen Jelstad, has informed the President of Serbia of 5 million [[euro]]s of aid aimed at combating the [[pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.republika.rs/vesti/srbija/194332/video-norveska-daje-srbiji-miliona-evra-borbu-protiv-korone-vucic-jelstad-donaciji|title=(VIDEO) Norve\u0161ka daje Srbiji 5 miliona evra za borbu protiv korone! Vu\u010di\u0107 i Jelstad o donaciji|website=REPUBLIKA|language=sr|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tanjug.rs/full-view.aspx?izb=543554|title=TANJUG {{!}} Norve\u0161ka Srbiji 5 mil evra,Vu\u010di\u0107:Hvala na ogromnoj pomo\u0107i|website=www.tanjug.rs|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|Russia}} has donated [[Serbia]] 15,000 [[COVID-19 testing|COVID-19 tests]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kurir.rs/vesti/drustvo/3434927/stigla-pomoc-iz-rusije-iz-moskve-u-beograd-stiglo-15000-testova-za-koronu|title=U SRBIJU STIGLA POMO\u0106 IZ RUSIJE: Moskva poslala u Beograd 15.000 testova za koronu|last=|first=|date=|website=Kurir.rs|language=Serbian|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> [[Russian Air Force]] has also flown 11 [[Il-76]] planeholds of medical experts, large amount of medical equipment, technical and protective gear and 16 motor vehicles for disinfection of facilities and roads to Serbia to help it fight the coronavirus spread.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rs.n1info.com/English/NEWS/a585464/Russia-sends-assistance-for-Serbia-to-fight-coronavirus.html|title=Eleven airplanes of Russia's aid for fight agst coronavirus arrive in Belgrade|website=N1 Srbija|language=|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|European Union}} have donated 7.5 million [[euro]]s aimed at expanding the capacity and improving the capabilities of combating the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]]. On March 26th, the [[European Union|EU]] have financed the aid flight from China. Further 94 million euros have been aimed at combating the pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rs.n1info.com/Vesti/a582423/Stigao-jos-jedan-avion-sa-medicinskom-opremom-iz-Kine-let-finansirala-EU.html|title=Stigao jo\u0161 jedan avion sa medicinskom opremom iz Kine, let finansirala EU|website=N1 Srbija|language=sr-Latn|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rtv.rs/sr_ci/politika/pomoc-eu-od-7-5-miliona-evra-za-borbu-protiv-koronavirusa_1104992.html|title=\u041f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u045b \u0415\u0423 \u043e\u0434 7,5 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0435\u0432\u0440\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0440\u0431\u0443 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430|last=\u0412\u043e\u0458\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0435|first=\u0408\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0458\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0443\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0408\u041c\u0423 \u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e-\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0458\u0430|website=\u0408\u041c\u0423 \u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e-\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u0458\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0435|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rs.n1info.com/Vesti/a581812/Vlada-EU-odobrila-Srbiji-prenamenu-94-miliona-evra-za-borbu-protiv-pandemije.html|title=Vlada: EU odobrila Srbiji prenamenu 94 miliona evra za borbu protiv pandemije|website=N1 Srbija|language=sr-Latn|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>. On the same day Swedish diplomat and former [[Prime Minister of Sweden|Prime Minister]] [[Carl Bildt]] have made remarks on [[Aleksandar Vu\u010di\u0107|Vu\u010di\u0107]]'s stance on the European aid compared to the Chinese.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rs.n1info.com/Vesti/a582639/Bilt-Vucic-pravio-sou-za-avion-iz-Kine-a-kada-stigne-pomoc-od-EU-nema-ga-nigde.html|title=Bilt: Vu\u010di\u0107 pravio \u0161ou za avion iz Kine, a kada stigne pomo\u0107 od EU nema ga nigde|website=N1 Srbija|language=sr-Latn|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> {{Quote|text=When China sent an aircraft with help to Serbia President Vu\u010di\u0107 made a great show of it. But when far more substantial aid arrives there is no fanfare and no President in sight.|author=Carl Bildt|title=|source=http://rs.n1info.com/Vesti/a582639/Bilt-Vucic-pravio-sou-za-avion-iz-Kine-a-kada-stigne-pomoc-od-EU-nema-ga-nigde.html}}\n[[Prime Minister of Serbia|Serbian PM]] [[Ana Brnabi\u0107]] accused Carl Bildt for spreading of fake news, because the medical aid was partially donated by China and partially bought by Serbia and the flight was paid by the EU.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/anabrnabic/status/1243553869067694085/|title=@anabrnabic|website=Twitter|language=sr-Latn|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|United Arab Emirates}} have donated 10 tons of medical aid.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nedeljnik.rs/u-beograd-sleteo-jos-jedan-avion-sa-medicinskom-pomoci-donacija-ujedinjenih-arapskih-emirata-docekao-ga-vulin/|title=U Beograd sleteo jo\u0161 jedan avion sa medicinskom opremom, donacija Ujedinjenih Arapskih Emirata|website=Nedeljnik|language=sr-Latn|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|Turkey}} have donated 100,000 protective masks, 2,000 protective suits, and 1,500 Covid19 testing kits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraf.rs/english/3176118-we-stand-with-serbia-in-this-difficult-time-plane-with-medical-aid-from-turkey-lands-in-belgrade|title=\"We stand with Serbia in this difficult time\": Plane with medical aid from Turkey lands in Belgrade\n|website=telegraf.rs|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|United States}} have donated 6,000 coronavirus test kits for the Serbian health care system.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rs.n1info.com/English/NEWS/a587091/US-Ambassador-pledges-coronavirus-test-kits-for-Serbia.html|title=US Ambassador pledges coronavirus test kits for Serbia|website=rs.n1info.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n\n===Personal donations===\n* Retired tennis player [[Ana Ivanovi\u0107]] donated 35 ventilators and medical aid packages.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rs.n1info.com/Sport-Klub/Tenis/a582237/Ana-Ivanovic-donirala-respiratore-Srbiji.html|title=Ana Ivanovi\u0107 donirala respiratore Srbiji|website=N1 Srbija|language=sr-Latn|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* Football manager [[Dejan Stankovi\u0107]] and his business partner Dragan Ruvarac donated ventilators and medical equipment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rtv.rs/sr_lat/drustvo/dejan-stankovic-donirao-respiratore-za-srbiju_1104880.html|title=Dejan Stankovi\u0107 donirao respiratore za Srbiju|last=Vojvodine|first=Javna medijska ustanova JMU Radio-televizija|website=JMU Radio-televizija Vojvodine|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n*World No. 1 tennis player [[Novak Djokovic|Novak \u0110okovi\u0107]] donated 1 million euros for ventilators and medical aid packages.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sportklub.rs/Tenis/ATP/a327864-Djokovic-donira-milion-evra-za-respiratore-u-Srbiji.html|title=\u0110okovi\u0107 donira milion evra za respiratore u Srbiji|website=Sport Klub SR|language=sr-Latn-RS|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n*NBA players [[Nemanja Bjelica]], [[Bogdan Bogdanovi\u0107 (basketball)|Bogdan Bogdanovi\u0107]] and basketball executive [[Vlade Divac]] have donated ventilators, masks and medical equipment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.politika.rs/scc/clanak/451777/Sport/Kosarka/Divac-Bogdanovic-i-Bjelica-salju-pomoc-za-Srbiju|title=\u0414\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0446, \u0411\u043e\u0433\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u045b \u0438 \u0411\u0458\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u0448\u0430\u0459\u0443 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u045b \u0437\u0430 \u0421\u0440\u0431\u0438\u0458\u0443|website=Politika Online|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n== Early reaction controversy ==\nSeeing as [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Coronavirus]] spread throughout Europe, on February 26. president [[Aleksandar Vu\u010di\u0107]] called for a press conference where he addressed the possibility of the virus impacting [[Serbia]]. This news conference made headlines the following days after a [[pulmonologist]] Dr. Branimir Nestorovi\u0107 made joking statements about the virus, calling it \"the most laughable virus in the history of mankind\" and suggested that women should travel to then virus-affected [[Italy]] for shopping. The president, who was visible in the background expressing amusement and chuckling at this during the TV broadcast, later denied any accusations of portraying the virus as such by Dr Nestorovi\u0107.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraf.tv/vesti/32235-vucic-o-vestima-da-je-korona-virus-stigao-u-srbiju|title=Vu\u010di\u0107 o vestima da je korona virus stigao u Srbiju|website=Telegraf.tv|language=sr|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.istinomer.rs/izjava/nemojte-da-lazete-niko-nije-rekao-da-je-korona-najsmesniji-virus/|title=Nemojte da la\u017eete, niko nije rekao da je korona najsme\u0161niji virus|website=Istinomer|language=sr-RS|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref><br />\n{{Quote|text=I cannot believe that the same people, who survived sanctions, bombing, the day-to-day bullying of all kinds, can get scared by the most laughable virus in the history of mankind, which [only] exists on Facebook.|author=Dr. Branimir Nestorovi\u0107|title=\nNemojte da la\u017eete, niko nije rekao da je korona najsme\u0161niji virus|source=https://www.istinomer.rs/izjava/nemojte-da-lazete-niko-nije-rekao-da-je-korona-najsmesniji-virus/}}{{Quote|text=I appeal to the people to stop trusting unproven information. The epidemic in China is at its end, it started on 7 December [2019] when the first case was reported. It is already known that virulence of the virus is in decline, hence the virus becomes more and more weak as the time passes by. But the virus is weak in any case. Here's something regarding women... The estrogen definitely  protects women, they have mild symptoms and they don't die from this virus. So, women, you can go shopping to Italy, I've heard that, now, there will be huge discounts there, because now nobody wants to go to Italy. So, prepare your husbands mentally for that. I am joking, but for real, I think, I don't understand. Couple of days ago I was shocked when that story (about the virus) started because the virus itself was laughable. This is the third variant of SARS and MERS, the corona viruses, this is the third variant and is the weakest of all three. The first two went unnoticed, and now, suddenly, this third one... I see now borders are being closed, planes don't fly... An absolute nonsense.|author=Dr. Branimir Nestorovi\u0107|title=Nemojte da la\u017eete, niko nije rekao da je korona najsme\u0161niji virus|source=https://www.istinomer.rs/izjava/nemojte-da-lazete-niko-nije-rekao-da-je-korona-najsmesniji-virus/}}\n\nIn April 2020, a decree that limited access to public information about COVID-19 was announced, but after public reaction it was revoked. The declared goal of the decree was to limit the spread of fake news about the coronavirus in Serbia.<ref name=\"tanjug1c\">{{cite news |title=This is a state of war, but decree limiting release of information will be withdrawn |url=https://www.b92.net/eng/news/society.php?yyyy=2020&mm=04&dd=02&nav_id=108243 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |agency=Tanjug |date=2020 |ref=tanjug1c}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Health in Serbia]]\n* [[Healthcare in Serbia]]\n* [[Coronavirus]]\n* [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n* [[COVID-19 vaccine]]\n* [[COVID-19 drug development]]\n\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Serbia|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{notes\n| notes =\n{{efn\n| name = status\n| {{Kosovo-note}}\n}}\n}}\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Serbia| ]]\n", "name_user": "Easternmagic", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBy districts and towns", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Serbia"}
